description:
&lt;p&gt;An exciting opportunity has arisen to join the community Nursing team in the Llanelli locality working 22.5 hours a week as a Community Staff Nurse. We are looking for an enthusiastic Nurse with a passion for nursing to join our friendly team.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You will possess excellent communication skills, enjoy working as part of a team, be able to work independently, carry out comprehensive assessments, plan, implement and evaluate delivery of complex nursing interventions as part of the holistic approach. Care will be delivered in patients&#39; own homes and residential settings&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The Community team is dedicated to support your continued professional development through various opportunities. The post will enhance your knowledge and open opportunities for further progression within our directorate.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;If you are dynamic, organised, work well within the multi-disciplinary team and have an interest in caring for people in their own home with various chronic, long term conditions and end of life care, we would like to hear from you.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The ability and means to travel between patients in a timely manner is essential.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The ability to speak Welsh is desirable for this post. English and /or Welsh speakers are equally welcome to apply.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Interviews will be held on 12th November 2020&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
